CONTRIBUTING.md
     3‚Üí# Contributing
     4‚Üí
     5‚Üí## Code of Conduct
     6‚Üí
     7‚ÜíAll interactions in the **npm** organization on GitHub are considered to be covered by our standard [Code of Conduct](https://docs.npmjs.com/policies/conduct).
     8‚Üí
     9‚Üí## Reporting Bugs
    10‚Üí
    11‚ÜíBefore submitting a new bug report please search for an existing or similar report.
    12‚Üí
    13‚ÜíUse one of our existing issue templates if you believe you've come across a unique problem.
    14‚Üí
    15‚ÜíDuplicate issues, or issues that don't use one of our templates may get closed without a response.
    16‚Üí
    17‚Üí## Pull Request Conventions
    18‚Üí
    19‚Üí### Commits
    20‚Üí
    21‚ÜíWe use [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/).
    22‚Üí
    23‚ÜíWhen opening a pull request please be sure that either the pull request title, or each commit in the pull request, has one of the following prefixes:
    24‚Üí
    25‚Üí - `feat`: For when introducing a new feature.  The result will be a new semver minor version of the package when it is next published.
    26‚Üí - `fix`: For bug fixes. The result will be a new semver patch version of the package when it is next published.
    27‚Üí - `docs`: For documentation updates.  The result will be a new semver patch version of the package when it is next published.
    28‚Üí - `chore`: For changes that do not affect the published module.  Often these are changes to tests.  The result will be *no* change to the version of the package when it is next published (as the commit does not affect the published version).
    29‚Üí
    30‚Üí### Test Coverage
    31‚Üí
    32‚ÜíPull requests made against this repo will run `npm test` automatically.  Please make sure tests pass locally before submitting a PR.
    33‚Üí
    34‚ÜíEvery new feature or bug fix should come with a corresponding test or tests that validate the solutions. Testing also reports on code coverage and will fail if code coverage drops.
    35‚Üí
    36‚Üí### Linting
    37‚Üí
    38‚ÜíLinting is also done automatically once tests pass.  `npm run lintfix` will fix most linting errors automatically.
    39‚Üí
    40‚ÜíPlease make sure linting passes before submitting a PR.
    41‚Üí
    42‚Üí## What _not_ to contribute?
    43‚Üí
    44‚Üí### Dependencies
    45‚Üí
    46‚ÜíIt should be noted that our team does not accept third-party dependency updates/PRs.  If you submit a PR trying to update our dependencies we will close it with or without a reference to these contribution guidelines.
    47‚Üí
    48‚Üí### Tools/Automation
    49‚Üí
    50‚ÜíOur core team is responsible for the maintenance of the tooling/automation in this project and we ask contributors to not make changes to these when contributing (e.g. `.github/*`, `.eslintrc.json`, `.licensee.json`).  Most of those files also have a header at the top to remind folks they are automatically generated.  Pull requests that alter these will not be accepted.
README.md
     4‚Üí## Note
     5‚Üí
     6‚Üí-   Sections are treated as nested objects.
     7‚Üí
     8‚Üí-   Section-less items are treated as globals.
     9‚Üí
    10‚Üí## Usage
    11‚Üí
    12‚ÜíConsider an INI file such as the following:
    13‚Üí
    14‚Üí```ini
    15‚Üí; This comment is being ignored
    16‚Üíscope = global
    17‚Üí
    18‚Üí[database]
    19‚Üíuser = dbuser
    20‚Üípassword = dbpassword
    21‚Üídatabase = use_this_database
    22‚Üí
    23‚Üí[paths.default]
    24‚Üídatadir = /var/lib/data
    25‚Üíarray[] = first value
    26‚Üíarray[] = second value
    27‚Üíarray[] = third value
    28‚Üí```
    29‚Üí
    30‚ÜíYou can **read**, **modify** and **write** it like so:
    31‚Üí
    32‚Üí```js
    33‚Üíimport { writeFile , readFile } from 'node:fs/promises'
    34‚Üíimport { stringify , parse } from 'ini'
    35‚Üí
    36‚Üí//  Read INI file as text
    37‚Üí
    38‚Üílet text = await readFile(`./Original.ini`,{
    39‚Üí    encoding : 'utf-8'
    40‚Üí})
    41‚Üí
    42‚Üí//  Parse text data to object
    43‚Üí
    44‚Üíconst config = parse(text)
    45‚Üí
    46‚Üí//  Modify data object
    47‚Üí
    48‚Üíconfig.scope = 'local'
    49‚Üíconfig.database.database = 'use_another_database'
    50‚Üíconfig.paths.default.tmpdir = '/tmp'
    51‚Üídelete config.paths.default.datadir
    52‚Üíconfig.paths.default.array.push('fourth value')
    53‚Üí
    54‚Üí//  Stringify data object
    55‚Üí
    56‚Üítext = stringify(config,{ 
    57‚Üí    section : 'section' 
    58‚Üí})
    59‚Üí
    60‚Üí//  Write INI file as text
    61‚Üí
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
    82‚Üí## API
    83‚Üí
    84‚Üí### Parse
    85‚Üí
    86‚ÜíAttempts to turn the given INI string into a nested data object.
    87‚Üí
    88‚Üí```js
    89‚Üí// You can also use `decode`
    90‚Üíconst object = parse(`<INI Text>`) 
    91‚Üí```
    92‚Üí
    93‚Üí### Stringify
    94‚Üí
    95‚ÜíEncodes the given data object as an INI formatted string.
    96‚Üí
    97‚Üí```js
    98‚Üí// You can also use `encode`
    99‚Üístringify(object,{
   100‚Üí
   101‚Üí    /**
   102‚Üí     *  Whether to insert spaces before & after `=`
   103‚Üí     * 
   104‚Üí     *  Disabled by default to have better 
   105‚Üí     *  compatibility with old picky parsers.
   106‚Üí     */
   107‚Üí
   108‚Üí    whitespace : false ,
   109‚Üí
   110‚Üí    /**
   111‚Üí     *  Whether to align the `=` character for each section.
   112‚Üí     *  -> Also enables the `whitespace` option
   113‚Üí     */
   114‚Üí
   115‚Üí    align : false ,
   116‚Üí
   117‚Üí    /**
   118‚Üí     *  Identifier to use for global items 
   119‚Üí     *  and to prepend to all other sections.
   120‚Üí     */
   121‚Üí
   122‚Üí    section ,
   123‚Üí
   124‚Üí    /**
   125‚Üí     *  Whether to sort all sections & their keys alphabetically.
   126‚Üí     */
   127‚Üí
   128‚Üí    sort : false ,
   129‚Üí
   130‚Üí    /**
   131‚Üí     *  Whether to insert a newline after each section header.
   132‚Üí     * 
   133‚Üí     *  The TOSHIBA & FlashAir parser require this format. 
   134‚Üí     */
   135‚Üí
   136‚Üí    newline : false ,
   137‚Üí
   138‚Üí    /**
   139‚Üí     *  Which platforms line-endings should be used.
   140‚Üí     * 
   141‚Üí     *  win32 -> CR+LF
   142‚Üí     *  other -> LF
   143‚Üí     * 
   144‚Üí     *  Default is the current platform
      ‚Üí‚Ä¶
   167‚Üí### Un / Escape
   168‚Üí
   169‚ÜíTurn the given string into a safe to  
   170‚Üíuse key or value in your INI file.
   171‚Üí
   172‚Üí```js
   173‚Üísafe(`"unsafe string"`) // -> \"unsafe string\"
   174‚Üí```
   175‚Üí
   176‚ÜíOr reverse the process with:
   177‚Üí
   178‚Üí```js
   179‚Üíunsafe(`\\"safe string\\"`) // -> "safe string"
   180‚Üí```
